After installing express I can use it in my app.js file like this:

=> const express = require('express');
=> const app = express();
 
=> app.get('/', (req, res) => {
=>  res.send('Hello World');
=> });
   
=> app.listen(3000, () => console.log('server works!'));

starting the application will give me:

=> server works // in terminal

going to localhost:3000 will give me:

=> Hello World // in page
